    33‚Üí/// A value in a key-value.
    34‚Üí///
    35‚Üí/// Values are an anonymous bag containing some structured datum.
    36‚Üí///
    37‚Üí/// # Capturing values
    38‚Üí///
    39‚Üí/// There are a few ways to capture a value:
    40‚Üí///
    41‚Üí/// - Using the `Value::from_*` methods.
    42‚Üí/// - Using the `ToValue` trait.
    43‚Üí/// - Using the standard `From` trait.
    44‚Üí///
    45‚Üí/// ## Using the `Value::from_*` methods
    46‚Üí///
    47‚Üí/// `Value` offers a few constructor methods that capture values of different kinds.
    48‚Üí///
    49‚Üí/// ```
    50‚Üí/// use log::kv::Value;
    51‚Üí///
    52‚Üí/// let value = Value::from_debug(&42i32);
    53‚Üí///
    54‚Üí/// assert_eq!(None, value.to_i64());
    55‚Üí/// ```
    56‚Üí///
    57‚Üí/// ## Using the `ToValue` trait
    58‚Üí///
    59‚Üí/// The `ToValue` trait can be used to capture values generically.
    60‚Üí/// It's the bound used by `Source`.
    61‚Üí///
    62‚Üí/// ```
    63‚Üí/// # use log::kv::ToValue;
    64‚Üí/// let value = 42i32.to_value();
    65‚Üí///
    66‚Üí/// assert_eq!(Some(42), value.to_i64());
    67‚Üí/// ```
    68‚Üí///
    69‚Üí/// ## Using the standard `From` trait
    70‚Üí///
    71‚Üí/// Standard types that implement `ToValue` also implement `From`.
    72‚Üí///
    73‚Üí/// ```
    74‚Üí/// use log::kv::Value;
    75‚Üí///
    76‚Üí/// let value = Value::from(42i32);
    77‚Üí///
    78‚Üí/// assert_eq!(Some(42), value.to_i64());
    79‚Üí/// ```
    80‚Üí///
    81‚Üí/// # Data model
    82‚Üí///
    83‚Üí/// Values can hold one of a number of types:
    84‚Üí///
